# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Express + DynamoDB app with CloudMock for local development.

## Getting Started

### 1. Start CloudMock

```bash
docker compose up
# or
npx cloudmock
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 3. Run the app

```bash
npm start
```

The server starts on http://localhost:3000.

## API

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | /items | Create / replace an item |
| GET | /items | List all items |
| GET | /items/:id | Get a single item |
| DELETE | /items/:id | Delete an item |

Example:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/items \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"id":"1","name":"Widget","price":9.99}'

curl http://localhost:3000/items/1
```

## Testing

```bash
npm test
```

Tests use `@cloudmock/sdk` to start an in-process CloudMock instance — no Docker required.

## CloudMock DevTools

Open [http://localhost:4500](http://localhost:4500) to explore traces, metrics, and request topology.
